## What changed and why
- Animation system (Animator, TextureAtlas, CharacterRenderer) fully moved to View layer under `View::Animations` namespace.
- Model layer no longer contains or references any Animator. Character and its subclasses are purely logical (position, velocity, health, direction, attack state).
- GameView now orchestrates CharacterRenderer::UpdateAll/RenderAll in the frame loop.
- Original Systems/AnimationSystem.* and Systems/TextureAtlas.* deleted — no code remains that includes them.

## Current status
- Complete. All animation responsibilities reside in View layer.
- FE can now use `View::CharacterRenderer` to register entities and drive their animation.
- BE can focus on pure game logic (Model) without visual dependencies.
